gameRecap.title: Game Recap: Spurs 116, Blazers 100
gameRecap.excerpt: The Spurs defeated the Blazers, 116-100. San Antonio had three players with double-doubles as Jeremy Sochan totaled 31 points along with a season-high 14 rebounds while Victor Wembanyama (23 points, 12 rebounds, two blocks) and Keldon Johnson (21 points, season-high 15 rebounds). Anfernee Simons led Portland with 40 points and 10 assists as Deandre Ayton added 20 points and 12 rebounds. The Spurs improve to 9-36 as the Blazers move to 13-32.
